  "prompt_text": "Prove that the square root of 2 is irrational.",
  "response_text": "To prove that the square root of 2 is irrational, we will use a proof by contradiction. This means we start by assuming the opposite of what we want to prove and then show that this assumption leads to a contradiction.\n\n**Proof:**\n\nAssume, for the sake of contradiction, that \\(\\sqrt{2}\\) is rational. By definition, a rational number can be expressed as a fraction \\(\\frac{a}{b}\\), where \\(a\\) and \\(b\\) are integers with no common factors other than 1 (i.e., the fraction is in its simplest form), and \\(b \\neq 0\\).\n\nSo, let's assume \\(\\sqrt{2} = \\frac{a}{b}\\), where \\(a\\) and \\(b\\) are coprime integers (they have no common factors other than 1).\n\nSquaring both sides of the equation, we get:\n\\[2 = \\frac{a^2}{b^2}\\]\n\nMultiplying both sides by \\(b^2\\) gives:\n\\[2b^2 = a^2\\]\n\nThis implies that \\(a^2\\) is even (since it is equal to \\(2\\) times another integer). Therefore, \\(a\\) must also be even (the square of an odd number is odd, so \\(a\\) cannot be odd if \\(a^2\\) is even). Let \\(a = 2k\\) for some integer \\(k\\).\n\nSubstituting \\(a = 2k\\) into the equation \\(2b^2 = a^2\\), we get:\n\\[2b^2 = (2k)^2 = 4k^2\\]\n\nDividing both sides by 2, we obtain:\n\\[b^2 = 2k^2\\]\n\nThis implies that \\(b^2\\) is even, and therefore \\(b\\) must also be even (for the same reason as above; the square of an odd number is odd, so \\(b\\) cannot be odd if \\(b^2\\) is even).\n\nSince both \\(a\\) and \\(b\\) are even, they share a common factor of 2, which contradicts our initial assumption that \\(a\\) and \\(b\\) have no common factors other than 1.\n\nTherefore, our original assumption that \\(\\sqrt{2}\\) is rational must be false. Hence, \\(\\sqrt{2}\\) is irrational.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precision): 9\nV (Verbal Fluency): 8\nG (Goal Directedness): 10\nP (Pattern Recognition): 7\nE (Epistemic Confidence): 9\nQ (Query Interpretation): 10\nC (Contextual Awareness): 8\nY (Affective Modeling): 7\nF (Flexibility): 6\nD (Depth of Processing): 9\n---END RATINGS---",
